After finishing fault milestone one and loving it, I kinda played this one expecting an even better visual novel from Alice in Dissonance, and they deleveried it. It started with a bang, literally, it blew my PC off, but I won't enter in any details.

Good points:
+character development, every character is improving in their own ways;
+story, they didn't progressed as much as I thought but I think they are taking their time setting all sorts of flags around the heroines;
+art is even better now compared to the first one;
+music blends perfectly with scenes;

-It still lack voice acting and I hope someday they add voice acting, some characters deserve it.
